<br>
I have gone ooc on occasion, and I am a hardcore roleplayer, so I know it happens. This person simply went about it all wrong.<br>
<br>
Besides, this particular question could easily have been asked in character.<br>
<br>
However, if you don't want to simply ignore the fellow, which can be construed as rude, then simply answer in character. He'll either get it, or he'll be the one standing there with his mouth hanging open.<br>
<br>
Basically, if someone does anything that hampers your enjoyment, you don't have to take it. You don't need to be rude about it either. It's all in fun.<br>
<br>
